# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Prefer NO plaintext passwords on disk
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Create a temporary file with real values (any name), same KEY=value shape
#    as below, including BETA_DJANGO_ADMIN_USERNAME and PASSWORD.
# 2. Copy it to .secrets.env, run:  bash setup_secrets.sh
#    When asked, delete the plain .secrets.env (Y) — credentials live in .secrets.enc only.
# 3. Decryption key for .secrets.enc — pick ONE (Flask/Gunicorn load these from .secrets.env):
#    • Add ONE line below (same passphrase as setup_secrets.sh): SECRETS_DECRYPTION_KEY=your-passphrase
#    • Or project file .secrets.key (one line, chmod 600)
#    • Or export SECRETS_DECRYPTION_KEY before starting the server
# 4. Optional: keep URLs in .secrets.env; usernames/passwords can live only inside .secrets.enc once decrypt works.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: public-ish URLs only (no passwords). Safe to keep locally; still gitignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
BETA_DJANGO_ADMIN_URL=https://nkb-backend-ccbp-beta.earlywave.in/admin/
PROD_DJANGO_ADMIN_URL=https://nkb-backend-ccbp-prod-apis.ccbp.in/admin/

# Do not put real passwords in this file if you use .secrets.enc + .secrets.key:
# BETA_DJANGO_ADMIN_USERNAME=
# BETA_DJANGO_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
# PROD_DJANGO_ADMIN_USERNAME=
# PROD_DJANGO_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Optional: Jupyter / other scripts
# BETA_JUPYTER_PASSWORD=
# PROD_JUPYTER_PASSWORD=

# Optional: if evaluation metrics admin URL 404s in your environment
# DJANGO_EVAL_METRICS_MODEL_PATH=nkb_question/codingquestiontestcaseevalutionmetrics/

# Required for .secrets.enc if you do NOT use .secrets.key (teammates: uncomment and set — private repo only):
# SECRETS_DECRYPTION_KEY=same-passphrase-as-setup_secrets.sh
# SECRETS_DECRYPTION_KEY_FILE=/path/to/keyfile
